You will give me your honest confession in my hand or I cannot keep you from the rope.

770
00:37:36,560 --> 00:37:37,560
Proctor does not reply.

771
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:39,560
What way do you go, Mr.

772
00:37:39,560 --> 00:37:40,560
Proctor?

773
00:37:40,560 --> 00:37:42,560
He has breast heaving his eyes staring.

774
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:45,560
Proctor tears the paper and crumbles it.

775
00:37:45,560 --> 00:37:48,560
And he is weeping in fury but erect.

776
00:37:48,560 --> 00:37:53,560
Marshall, Paris hysterically as though the tearing paper were his life.

777
00:37:53,560 --> 00:37:54,560
Proctor?

778
00:37:54,560 --> 00:37:55,560
Proctor?

779
00:37:55,560 --> 00:37:57,560
Man, you will hang.

780
00:37:57,560 --> 00:37:58,560
You cannot.

781
00:37:58,560 --> 00:38:00,560
Proctor is eyes full of tears.

782
00:38:00,560 --> 00:38:02,560
I can.

783
00:38:02,560 --> 00:38:06,560
And there's your first marvel that I can.

784
00:38:06,560 --> 00:38:12,560
You have made your magic now, for now I do think I see some shred of goodness in John Proctor.

785
00:38:12,560 --> 00:38:18,560
Not enough to weave a banner with but white enough to keep it from such dogs.

786
00:38:18,560 --> 00:38:22,560
Elizabeth, in a burst of tear, rushes to him and weeps against his hand.

787
00:38:22,560 --> 00:38:24,560
Give them note here.

788
00:38:24,560 --> 00:38:26,560
Tears pleasure them.

789
00:38:26,560 --> 00:38:31,560
Show honor now, show a stony heart and sink them with it.

790
00:38:31,560 --> 00:38:34,560
He has lifted her and kisses her now with great passion.

791
00:38:34,560 --> 00:38:36,560
Let you fear nothing.

792
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:38,560
Another judgment waits us all.

793
00:38:38,560 --> 00:38:40,560
Hang them high over the town.

794
00:38:40,560 --> 00:38:43,560
Who weeps for these weeps for corruption.

795
00:38:43,560 --> 00:38:45,560
He sweeps out past them.

796
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:48,560
Heric starts to lead Rebecca, who almost collapses.

797
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:53,560
But Proctor catches her and she glances up at him, apologetically.

798
00:38:53,560 --> 00:38:55,560
I've had no breakfast.

799
00:38:55,560 --> 00:38:56,560
Go, man.

800
00:38:56,560 --> 00:38:58,560
Heric escorts them out.

801
00:38:58,560 --> 00:39:00,560
Atheran and she ver behind them.

802
00:39:00,560 --> 00:39:03,560
Elizabeth stands staring at the empty doorway.

803
00:39:03,560 --> 00:39:05,560
Paris, intently fear, do Elizabeth.

804
00:39:05,560 --> 00:39:07,560
Go to him, go to him, go to him, go to him, go to him, go to him, go to him.

805
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:09,560
There is yet time.

806
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:12,560
From outside a drumroll strikes the air.

807
00:39:12,560 --> 00:39:13,560
Paris is startled.

808
00:39:13,560 --> 00:39:15,560
Elizabeth jerks about toward the window.

809
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:16,560
Go to him.

810
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:20,560
He rushes out the door as though to hold back his fate.

811
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:22,560
Proctor, Proctor!

812
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:25,560
Again, a short burst of trumps.

813
00:39:25,560 --> 00:39:27,560
Woman pleads with him.

814
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:30,560
He starts to rush out the door and then goes back to her.

815
00:39:30,560 --> 00:39:32,560
Woman, it is pride.

816
00:39:32,560 --> 00:39:33,560
It is vanity.

817
00:39:33,560 --> 00:39:36,560
She avoids his eyes and moves to the window.

818
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:37,560
He drops to his knees.

819
00:39:37,560 --> 00:39:39,560
Be his helper.

820
00:39:39,560 --> 00:39:41,560
What profit him to bleed?

821
00:39:41,560 --> 00:39:43,560
Shall the dust praise him?

822
00:39:43,560 --> 00:39:45,560
Shall the worms declare his truth?

823
00:39:45,560 --> 00:39:48,560
Go to him, take his shame away.

824
00:39:48,560 --> 00:39:54,560
Elizabeth, supporting herself against collapse, grips the bars of the window, and with a cry.

825
00:39:54,560 --> 00:39:56,560
He have his goodness now.

826
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:59,560
God forbid I take it from him.

827
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:03,560
The final drumroll crashes, then heightens violently.

828
00:40:03,560 --> 00:40:08,560
Hail weeps in front of prayer, and the new sun is pouring in upon her face.

829
00:40:08,560 --> 00:40:11,560
And the drums rattle like bones in the morning air.

830
00:40:11,560 --> 00:40:13,560
The curtain falls.